e of white knight on f3, this is a very principled way of attacking opponent's fianchetto, even in the opening.} 15. h4 { This weakens the g4-square, but the alternatives were even worse.} ( 16. h3 $6 {allows Black to create another dark-squared weakness with} h4 17. g4 Nh7 18. O-O Ng5 19. Nc3 c6 20. Kh1 Nge6 $15 {and Black was simply better in 0-1 (60) Mousavi,S (2432) -Edouard,R (2639) Guilan 2016}  ) Ng4 16. O-O {This position was reached in the game 1-0 (39) Esipenko,A (2672) -Najer,E (2661) Moscow 2020. We can improve on Black's play with} O-O $146 {  which promises very excellent counterplay play in the following variations:} 17. Kh1 ( 18. Nc3 f5 19. exf5 Nxf5 20. Bg5 Qd7 21. Ne4 c6 $15  ) ( 18. Bg5 Qd7 19. c5 a5 $132  ) Ne6 18. Qe1 {and here we have a couple of promising options:} Nf4 $5 ( {and} b5 $13  ) 19. Nb2 f5 $132  *

